# Model config: Qwen3-Coder-Next (UD-Q5_K_M, sharded GGUF) -- model-intrinsic only.
#
# 80B MoE, ~3B active (512 experts, 10 used). The UD-Q5_K_M weights total ~55 GiB
# across three shards; point -m at the FIRST shard and llama.cpp loads the rest.
#
# This file holds ONLY what is intrinsic to the model (weight path + sampling).
# How it fits a given card -- context, KV quant, split -- is GPU-specific and
# lives in profiles/<machine>/qwen3-coder-next.env.
#
# Sampling (verified 2026-07-17 against the Qwen model card + Unsloth docs):
#   Qwen:    temp 1.0, top-p 0.95, top-k 40 (non-thinking model, no <think>).
#   Unsloth: min-p 0.01 (llama.cpp defaults min-p to 0.05 -- must be lowered),
#            repeat penalty disabled (1.0; explicit because we used to set 1.05).
# The previous temp 0.7 / top-p 0.8 / top-k 20 / rp 1.05 recipe here was the
# Qwen3-Coder-480B recommendation, not this model's.

: "${MODEL:=Qwen3-Coder-Next/UD-Q5_K_M/Qwen3-Coder-Next-UD-Q5_K_M-00001-of-00003.gguf}"

LLAMA_ARGS+=(--temp 1.0 --top-p 0.95 --top-k 40 --min-p 0.01 --repeat-penalty 1.0)
LLAMA_ARGS+=(--alias qwen3-coder-next)
